** I changed the address, it's now hosted on my own server instead of my ISP, should be more reliable, apologies for the incovenience. -- LucasBonnet.
** The address changed again, now hosted on the wiki, my DSL doesn't like Summer. -- LucasBonnet
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/alex/beige-red.css Beige Red CSS] Beige background, large text, looks like (to me) an old newspaper. Not recommended for viewing code.
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/css/beige-red-test.css Compact Antique Beige]: Like Antique Beige but less whitespace. Not recommended for viewing code.
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/css/lukhas.css;theme=beige Beige + Small Font CSS]
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/css/blue.css Blue more text]: Similar to the default skin but with less whitespace so more fits on one page.
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/css/wiki_blue.css;theme=blue Blue + Small Font CSS] Another color. I can't live without Blue :)
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=http://www.physik.fu-berlin.de/~dhansen/css/wiki.css Grey and Red]
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/community/green.css Green CSS]
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/css/astrid.css Beige CSS] Larger font with earth tones.
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/oddmuse/grey.css Grey CSS] by "mad" of the [http://czlug.madbrains.net/wiki/wiki.pl czlug]
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/paper/wiki.css Paper CSS] -- This is a CSS that might be useful when using a wiki to prepare papers. It is useless for day-to-day browsing, in my not-so-humble opinion.
* [http://iki.fi/juhtolv/css-download/ Stylesheets] of JuhapekkaTolvanen combined with the [http://www.emacswiki.org/css/emacs.css Default CSS] ('''If you really adopt some of these stylesheets, it would be nice to hear about it! Other comment are welcome, too!'''):
** [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/css/emacs.css%20http://iki.fi/juhtolv/index.css;theme=juhtolv-index index] : Green text on black
** [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/css/emacs.css%20http://iki.fi/juhtolv/indexbw.css;theme=juhtolv-indexbw indexbw] : Black text on white
** [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/css/emacs.css%20http://iki.fi/juhtolv/indexbwserif.css;theme=juhtolv-indexbwserif indexbwserif] : Black serif font text on white
** [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/css/emacs.css%20http://iki.fi/juhtolv/latex;theme=juhtolv-latex latex] : Black LaTeX font on white (Download cm-super from CTAN, for example)
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/oddmuse/orange.css  Orange] of http://de.veganwiki.org
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=http://purl.org/NET/wence/emacswiki.css A white and blue] stylesheet that tries to keep page widths to around 70 to 80 characters, and flags up external links with a small image.
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=http://www.emacswiki.org/alex/wikio.css;theme= white on blue and cyan links]-- discovered on EarleMartin's site after reading about his [http://downlode.org/log/2005-01-14/Mu_License Mu License] and adapted for Oddmuse by AlexSchroeder.
** ([EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=http://www.emacswiki.org/alex/wikio.css;theme=bigger Same thing, but 100ex wide])
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/css/cali.css;theme= Designed in California] -- It was inspired by all these sites featuring software for Mac OSX.  Strange how so many of these sites seem to be inspired by the Apple website.  I basically looked at the [http://www.ethomaz.com/onlife/ Onlife] site style sheet for font family and size, some basic whitespace distribution, and added the rest to make it all work for Oddmuse.
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/css/pink-bliss.css;theme= Pink Bliss] -- Inspired by the ColorTheme PinkBliss
* [EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/css/basic.css%20/css/twb.css;theme= twb's favorite CSS]

'''Additions to the list welcome!'''

Note that due to security considerations, most browsers will prevent you from loading a style sheet from a different server.
